Program: Outlook
Title: From child soldier to Franciscan monk
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0106bhh
Last Broadcast Date: Thu 15 Nov 2012
Respected Peruvian anthropologist Lurgio Gavilan describes his life as a child soldier for the Shining Path rebel group and his journey to becoming a Franciscan monk. Also, Derek Amato explains how banging his head on the bottom of a swimming pool meant that he could suddenly play the piano. And Matthew meets South African ballerina Clair Symonds who once danced for the Shah of Iran. Image: Lurgio Gavilan (l) when he was in the Peruvian military, with a colleague and a donkey Show less